< review>
Probably one of the best dental experiences I've had. Everyone here is real friendly and has good bedside manner. Recently I went in for a root canal and found the experience to be far less intense than I thought it was going to be. But before that work was to be done, I had to get a cleaning. Their hygienist Marie Rand worked on my teeth. What a nice gal, and her bedside manner is top notch. I was receiving a scaling and root cleaning/planing, which kinda hurts. But Marie was real professional and wiped it out in no time. I highly recommend Moorpark Dental Group and plan on continuing to go there.< /review>

< username>
Martha Montelongo< /username>
< Date>
1482518075306< /Date>
<rate>1<//rate>< Review>
BUYER BEWARE--They bait and switch you from an offer too good to be true, for a plan so expensive, you'll need financing or to break into your emergency savings to pay for it.

I moved to Moorpark  in 2015 and was way overdue for my routine six-month cleaning and check-up, but since this has been an aberration in my overall adult life of dental healthcare maintenance, I was surprised with the first-time new-patient examination findings.

I went to the clinic thinking this was a great deal--an exam, x-rays, and a cleaning for a low price of $59.00.   Their disclaimer that you only get the cleaning if you don't have periodontal disease didn't concern me, as I was confident that didn't apply to me.   A simple ordinary tell-tale sign is my gums don't bleed when I floss, which is daily, no less than once a day, though often more often, to remove any food stuck between my teeth.

The x-rays were a cheap quality and type, and several of the tooth images didn't come out and so the technician kept repeating them, giving me more radiation exposure each time, and until I realized this was a chronic issue with either the machine or the software.   At first I was very cooperative and flexible.  But when it became several times where the machine wouldn't perform, I lost faith in the equipment they were using and in their process.

Then I got the exam from the dentist, who was very cordial and friendly and made great small talk.   He said all my crowns, and fillings looked fine.   He told me what I knew, about my receding gum lines, something I was aware of and have always been told can be managed with good oral hygiene and diet.  But then he told me the bad news.   I had severe periodontal disease so I couldn't get the cleaning I had come in to receive.   The dentist said I needed laser cleaning and resurfacing  or planing, or something like that--a procedure that would cost me thousands of dollars.    Then then handed me off to their financing and scheduling plan coordinator.

I was upset and said thanks but no thanks and I got a second opinion from another dentist in town.

I needed a cleaning, and I welcomed a real exam and set of x-rays that were clear and complete.

It is my personal opinion that Moorpark Dental Group and Orthodontics is a scam.  I feel I got ripped-off  with their bait and switch from an offer for a very inexpensive exam, x-rays and a cleaning for a price too good to be true, to reel me into a very expensive and questionable treatment I didn't want or need.

BUYER BEWARE!   If they tell you you need their laser treatment for periodontal disease, hold onto your wallet and go get a second opinion.  I feel really ripped off.   I want my money back.<//Review>

Great spot for a cold treat, ice cream flavors are the real deal. The ones I have tried have been good, you can taste the natural fruit/nutty taste. Place was empty when I visited, some street parking available in front or there is a lot in the back of establishment. Pops is one of my favorite ice cream places.  Their ice cream are made of most exotic fruits.  Every flavor is delicious and bring childhood comforting memories.  Due to this reason I had decided that they had to cater for my sons first birthday Party.  The owner Marthin made sure to answer all my questions.  Make flavor accommodations, they had the patience serving our family and friends, explaining of flavors and ingredients used , while serving.  I could not ask for more.  Marthin and his staff were an amazing success and hit for this birthday party.  The catering price was reasonable for 100 ppl. Compliments have not stopped since.  I could not ask for more. < review>
Absolutely the best place to get ice cream in the San Fernando Valley, and perhaps all of Southern California!!! Every flavor that's created, seems to come straight from the depths of their heart. There is so much passion in every single flavor and each and every scoop! I love the sincere energy and extraordinary customer service! I always feel like a friend when I walk in, and family by the time I walk out!

Rudy, Marthin, Damon and the rest of the awesome crew go above and beyond to make sure I'm choosing the best flavor ice cream (or combination of flavors) for the day... and they get it right every time!

Never have I felt so excited to visit a place for ice cream until I discovered POPS!!! I highly recommend the ice cream, family sport, and the life changing experience shared among the most uniquely created flavors in the world!!! Hands down one of my absolute favorite places!! Oh yeah, two more words: Yum Yum!!!<//review>

<text>Helados Pops deserves the #1 title for ice cream and sorbet in L.A., and for reasons beyond the sweet treats they offer. I've become a regular after randomly stopping by to satisfy a sweet tooth during my search for top quality local spots. My expectations were shattered and it was hard to believe that I just happened to cross paths with this gem.

Pops far exceeds other ice cream shops for a few reasons: unusual & exotic flavors, skillful & passionate ice cream making, and a true passion & closeness that extends beyond the business and to the customers. Marthin, Damon, Rudy, and the rest of the team make you feel like family with every visit.

If you're looking to cool off in the L.A. heat, Pops is highly recommended, and not just for the cold treats--but for intricately strategized ice cream and sorbet flavors you've never had, as well as a welcoming atmosphere with people who will talk with you and even educate you during your visit.< /text><Pics>None< /Pics>< Resp>

< text>
I pass by this ice cream shop all the time, it's on maclay so if I'm riding my scooter around town I always come up this street.
I'm soo glad and not glad I did lol

-glad because they have some awesome flavors
-not glad because I'm gonna gain weight now that I know they have amazing flavors lol, so close to where I live.

I waked in and was greeted by a guy which instantly wanted me to try different flavors lol.
I DID not object hahaha
I literally almost tried everything and ended up taking home:
Nance!
Mango!
Horchata! And Lucuma!

Yumm
Reasonably priced not like the crazy expensive ice cream joints popping up everywhere.
Local business.

It's great to try if you are around San Fernando</text>

<Text>I live in LA where they are many Chevy dealers & ended up driving 200 miles north to purchase my Camaro ZL1 from Madera Chevy. That should tell you how they treated me.
From the time when I first contacting this dealer inquiring about the car, through making the deal, taking delivery & follow up calls afterwards to make sure I was taken care off.
Everybody I dealt with conducted themselves very professionally, did exactly what they said they would. Which is not so common nowadays.
There were not so many of this model car Camaro ZL1 available here in LA, most of the local dealers in LA had an additional markup over MSRP - which nobody wants to pay more than sticker.
Madera Chevy were not so greedy & offered a fair price on the car.
I have purchased over 25 new commercial & personal vehicles over the last 30 years and this dealership is one of the most professional & easy to conducted business with.

Both John in fleet Dept & Robert in Sales Dept, went out of their way to help me.
I did most of the paperwork over the phone & via email with Angela's help from the customer service dept.
Very fair competitive pricing and excellent customer service,

Some of the local chevy dealers here in LA should take some lessons from Madera chevy in how to treat potential customers. There was no hard selling or playing any games.
Just a fair, honest deal without any of the LA car buying drama.

In the past, I would never spent the time to write reviews on any given business.
But as a business owner myself, I appreciate & respect a well ran business & felt this company was worth taking the time to share my experience with other potential car buyers..
There are still some car dealers out there that conduct themselves with some oil fasion good values.

It was well worth the drive back, enjoying our new Camaro & avoiding tickets.
I would recommend checking this dealer out if you're in the market for a new chevy car, they also have a Toyota dealership as well.
Good luck.</Text>< Pics>

Madera Auto Center's slogan is "We'll Keep You Coming Back." After recently purchasing a car here, my family and I can confidently say that the staff at Madera truly live up to that slogan because of the experience that far exceeded our expectations.

When I contacted Madera Auto Center about the car I wanted, I was already impressed with the correspondence between Lisa Dodd and I because she was so polite, professional, and knowledgeable. She was such a pleasure to work with, and because of that we did not hesitate to work with the dealership despite being 130 miles away from them.

Unfortunately, we never got to meet Lisa because she was on vacation, but I'm glad to say our positive experience was maintained when she referred us over to Direct Salesperson Houa Xiong, who was really personable, well-mannered, and just a great person to work with! He had the car ready for us as soon as we arrived, and he made the transition into the finance office seamless. Lupe Martinez, the finance manager, explained the options for extended warranties/service packages and offered us packages that were actually catered to our needs. On our way back home we were even thanked by Lisa even though she was on vacation.

Madera Auto Center was a breath of fresh air compared to other dealerships. They are a family-owned business, and one of the few dealerships that still understands that the core of their business is based on the relationship with the customers. They really put their customers first, which was evident by the way Lisa, Houa, Lupe and the rest of the staff treated us when we bought our car.

I'm convinced that those who purchase a car will have an outstanding experience, and it will be so exceptional that they'll keep you coming back :).<//Text>

< Text>
I've been eating street tacos my whole life. From my childhood in South L.A. to the neighborhoods of the O.C. (yuck) and even as far as New York, Orlando and Chicago, I've had street tacos all over. < text>
Had install of two new split-system A/C + furnaces, and two new water heaters, in addition to an install of a new 80' gas line run to the meter to bring it up to code (previous line was installed improperly by another plumber). Alan's crew was hard-working, punctual, professional, efficient, and friendly.  Install quality was top-notch, and they did a great job cleaning up everything afterwards.  Would highly recommend.<//text>

< Text>
I simply cannot say enough positive things about Love's Heating & Air!  From start to finish - first touch to end of the project - Exceptional Customer Service and Customer-Focused.  My "Comfort Advisor" (how awesome a title is that?!?) Carl explained everything I had going on with my 18 year-old air conditioning system and what options I had to ensure I received the best outcomes all around.  The gentlemen who came out to do the work, and I do mean Gentlemen!, were outstanding individuals.  Jose, Juan, and Kyle - all 3 were a wonderful representation of what customer-focused service should look like.  Personable, hardworking, polite, kind, exceptionally clean and tidy in their work... like I said:  I cannot say enough positive things about my experience.  Thank you so much for all you do!  It was a wonderful experience to come home to a cool home!  Something I have not had for several weeks.  I appreciate you Love's Heating & Air!<//Text>

< text>
Loves replaced my 32 year old AC, furnace, and water heater on 8/4/21.  Matt, who is part owner, was very professional, yet personable and always promptly responded to my texts and phone calls.  Talk about a nice guy, when movers came unexpectedly during my consult to replace my refrigerator, Matt took it upon himself to help me to unload all of my food.
Alan, Ben, Nick and David, who were the crew that did the install, were a well oiled machine. Each member worked on their individual tasks, making the job go smoothly. All of them were friendly, respectful and didn't make me feel like an ignorant woman when I asked a question. I was impressed that all of the guys told me that they enjoyed working for Loves, which made me glad that I had chosen the right company that not only was good to it's customers, but also treated it's employees well.</text>

<rating>5< /rating>< review>
Carl, the system analyst was very thorough explaining our system needs and all the options to consider.  His bid was very competitive and work was set up in less than 1 week.
The service technicians (Jose, Joel and Alan) arrived professionally dressed, with clean uniforms and were very friendly during the entire day long project.  Despite the hot weather (98 degrees) they cheerfully completed the job as promised.  Clean up was thorough inside and out.

This place is a little Parisienne Oasis in the Desert. Feels like you were invited to an initimate backyard party at someones hip abode. The outdoor space Cafe style eating area is mostly protected from the harsh sun. The staff is quick with smiles and friendly service. I had the Chicken BLT and it hit the spot. <user_id>115726166085608492649<//user_id><user_name>J.W. Clark< /user_name><time>1619290037740<//time><rate>5< /rate><Text>Amazing, super fresh, huge portions and beyond delicious. I had the Andouille omelette with spinach and gruyere cheese. It came with roasted potatoes and a fresh soft baked baguette. My mouth was mesmerized! <Rating>1</Rating><time>1614312598186</time>< Text>
Ate here once for brunch and the food (ordered sandwiches and crepes) was mediocre, but the wait staff was nice. The owner is extremely rude and arrogant, not easy to work with for corporate or private events. We inquired about a potential group dinner as they had outdoor space, and wish we hadn't wasted our time. Plenty of great restaurants in the area with owners who respect their patrons and are easy to work with. If you believe in using your money to support good causes and kind small business owners, please go elsewhere!</Text>

Delicious!! Farm offers fresh fresh fresh food. The garden dining area is absolutely gorgeous. I wanted to move in. Herbs, roses, bougainvillea, morning glory vines, all growing and thriving all around. The music is soft and very Parisienne. I loved the cloth napkins and miss matched glassware spoke to my inner French bohemian. The coffee was yummy and iced to perfection. My favorite was the bacon. They get it by the slab and slice it themselves. It is uncured and the flavor is insane. I'm single so this bacon was the best part of my trip lol. I mean I don't even need romance if I can eat that bacon every day.. the staff was so friendly and honestly Farm will be my go to when in Palm Springs. Don't miss this restaurant!<//Text>

<Text>Bienvenue! An extraordinary French vibe and cuisine in the heart of Palm Springs. This family owned restaurant offers great Southern French breakfast and lunch that your palate will enjoy. No wonder it‚Äôs very popular among locals/tourists. It‚Äôs located in a huge plaza overlooking the mountain. We were warmly greeted by the hostess and escorted us to our table. You can feel the ubiquity of southern France atmosphere as you step inside the barn door. We were seated at the center of the outdoor patio restaurant right next to a wooden chandelier. <rate>2</rate>< text>
Yikes. The best thing going for this place is the location and setting in central PS in a pretty courtyard. But the food and service leave a lot to be desired. And French? Not at all.

Steak ordered medium rare and without mushrooms arrived well done, with mushrooms, 1 of which was rotten/inedible. Grilled salmon was essentially seared/raw (unclear how intentional this was but it looked and tasted terrible), sent back, next version same thing.

Server was not familiar with how the food was prepared. Manager was helpful and tried to improve the experience but to no avail. Maybe an "off night" but you have to wonder how such poorly cooked and executed food can slip through if manager/chef are paying attention at all.< /text>

<Rating>5< /Rating>< text>
Best dining experience of my life. Amazing five course meal and incredible service, but most of all was the atmosphere. Relaxed, but elegant and romantic. Lighting, mist and fans, foliage/flowers and mood lighting in a smaller alley like setting make it feel straight out of movie.

< Review>
One real vegan type of option but being a French restaurant it would be unreasonable to ask for more.

Food and mixed drinks are incredible. Social distancing, text comes when your table is ready, staff is always cleaning, the mist and hanging greenery keeps you cool and cozy in triple digit heat and you scan the menu on your phone.

They are tip top with preventive health measure. Service is great. I loved that the cutlery and glasses were all different, like it was someone's home.

Pricing is high.</Review>

<text>We recently went here for breakfast and a must to order is the banana fosters French toast = perfection! So delicious, not too sweet, and cooked perfectly. I wished I lived closer just so I could visit again and order the French toast. The bacon was crispy and tasty and I enjoyed my meal. The hubby's waffle was yummy too!

<userid>115508870264717846987<//userid>< user_name>
Denice Solorio< /user_name>
<Time>1537769809109< /Time><rating>5</rating>< Review>
This was the third time we have been to The Farm and it has been amazing everytime.  The food is always good, there really isn't much you can do with breakfast but its always fresh and yummy.  The fact that some how they make you feel like you are really on a farm is really cute, well done guys.  I love all the little touches with the pictures of the farm animals to rustic (non-matchey) furniture to the trained humming bird (see my photo) that stopped by our table. Food is part of the experience we (Me and Rob) enjoy of course, but it's the whole dining out process, service and the setting complete it.  The Farm has is figured out, Jerry Ayala ( Who is from our hometown too Orange) is great!! Hope to see you all real soon.<//Review>

Ok here we go last night was a success .
Presentation: I walked in to a very clean and cozy spot
Server : Crystal was amazing , running around like a chicken without a  head attending to our every need and ask  ( all alone we were a party of 15) had a big smile on her face and not once did she mess up on our order kept asking if we needed anything .
Cook : Jay took the time to come outside  to our table and tell us what was good on the menu apparently the chicken Posole and meatloaf were a hit .
Taste and quality on food :
Chicken Posole : great taste ! Authentic Mexican taste not to strong or plan on spices , the color was dark green how it's supposed to be and able to taste the different chiles , the texture  of the chicken was perfect .
Wagyu burger : meat was perfect ( medium rare ) just how I like it super juicy .
Fries : fat fries maybe could use a little more season salt .
Ranch dressing : home made delicious
Chicken Parmesan  : chicken was moist but not really flavorful not a fan or would  I recommend .
In general definitely 5 st< /review>

My family and I enjoyed our brunch at Farm!  It is a little difficult to find from the main road.  There isn‚Äôt a lot of parking nearby but it is a fun area to explore.  I suggest finding a parking spot and then walking to the restaurant because it is easier to find on foot. They had a great banana french toast with hazelnuts.  I enjoyed the watermelon lemonade and my mom loved the savory mushroom crepe.  These crepes looked darker than the typical white flour crepe.  I think they may be made from buckwheat flour which is a bit healthier.  The outdoor seating is very pretty and filled with flowers.<//text>

< review>
Great brunch place open for dinner only on weekends. Great location downtown on La Plaza just off the Palm Canyon. The location is in kind of a courtyard and has a nice French countryside atmosphere with many tables outdoors. Really good food and service. They do not take reservations and you should expect a wait. Stop in to put your name on the list and go shop or get a coffee nearby. They will text when your table is ready.</review>

This place is great from the amazing courtyard, to the staff and the food. If you are looking for a cute place to have a brunch this is it. There is a nice variety of unique food and drinks. I am so sorry to give only 3 stars to this beautiful restaurant because I really wanted to love it. The location, ambience and decor are amazing. The drinks are unique and great. All the people working there are so friendly, smiling and helpful. Our problem was the food. I had great expectations after reading the reviews, visiting the website and recommendations. <text>One of the best in the region
Farm Restaurant in Palm Springs is like a slice of European countryside, plopped in the center of town. With it's charming patio just of La Plaza, you would never know that you were in a city.
We've eaten there several times now and every meal was a joy. The young staff is very friendly and professional and the owner makes a point of making diners feel welcome.

< Text>
Where most of the people there were friendly the service I received was rushed and less than responsive. I asked for a simple breakfast of coffee and a waffle and was told waffles were only with the chicken and waffles or on the side . I said I will pay for the meal but I only want the waffle. What I got was under cooked chicken and almost a corner of a very small waffle that was cold. The coffee was also cool. After asking for the check and paying in cash the change took longer to get than the meal and it was short. I guess coin is rounded down.
All in all it was not a nice experience and I lived here. Maybe being from Pioneertown and not looking the part of a tourist makes a difference. As an organic farm and ranch owner I think this is not the best place to go.
I will be happy to cook real organic grown food for them just to taste the difference< /Text>

<time>1527639583894<//time><Rate>5</Rate>< review>
Awesome,  eclectic atmosphere and decor. Our server was attentive and knowledgeable about the menu,  even going above and beyond to ask about possible allergens  (there is no flour in the Bacon, Chicken and Waffles gravy, so this GF girl could have a bite of the chicken!) The Canard omelette was amazing and the individual french press coffee a nice touch.  A little spendy for breakfast,  but worth every penny.  A hidden gem in La Plaza well worth the visit!  We were able to walk in and be seated right away on a Tuesday,  but reservations might be a good idea on the weekend.</review>

I had strawberry crepes, orange juice and a wonderful cup of coffee. Everything was exquisite and our service very attentive and pleasant. I can't wait to go back!!</review>

<Text>We went this past weekend with a group of 7. We sat on the patio (wish they had fans, but that's our fault for sitting outside in Palm Springs in May). It was shaded, so that was nice! The wait was 45 minutes around 10:00 AM on a Saturday - so not too bad. The hostesses were really nice. We all liked our food, but our drinks ended up not coming until after we were done eating. We did put our food & drink order in at the same time, but I've never been to a restaurant in my life where the bar doesn't work faster than the kitchen. This obviously put our server in an uncomfortable position too, since we were clearly annoyed. We had to ask for the drinks to be comped, so they took 20% our check. I was happy they tried to fix the situation, but I would have preferred the discount was just offered or drinks comped instead of having to ask for it. Clearly no customer ever wants an entire meal to go by THEN be served their drink. Other than that, the food was good & our waiter was nice.< /Text>< Pictures>

<user_id>116295754258435175960</user_id><user_name>Amy F<//user_name>< date>
1562977893069< /date>
<Rating>4</Rating>< review>
It's a very cute garden atmosphere. The server in charge of water was on top of it. My water never even got to halfway. The server in charge of our food order was helpful about answering questions.
I got the smoked salmon, goat cheese, and spinach omelette. It was absolutely stuffed with smoked salmon. The goat cheese was inconsistent. I would have liked more goat cheese. I was not a fan of the raw spinach in the omelette. I would have preferred it cooked a bit. I really liked the omelette once I took out most of the spinach.
The side salad was mixed greens with (I think) some vinaigrette. The omelette also came with a big piece of a very tasty baguette.
After we finished our meal and our plates were removed, it took a while to get our bill. Or perhaps time just went slower in the heat.<//review>

< Review>
The farm transports you into a countryside indoor outdoor setting, greeting you with its charm and decor. Mismatched place settings add to that flavor. Even if you are not granted indoor tables, shade, fans, and hand powered fans keeps you cool.

The food is more French inspired than truly French as the baguette, a marker of the kitchen's adherence to quality was disappointing. There was no inspired crunch followed by a chewy doughy delight. (See omelet picture)

That being said, the ambience lends itself to feeling good as you eat a rustic American breakfast under gentle shade. Yes the Cobb salad was good, and avocado portions generous.</Review>

<text>Wonderful experience at FARM. We were quoted 45min wait and ended up being no more than 20min (which gave us just enough time to check out the neighbouring shops). <user>106867723869887076661< /user>< username>
Paul Metzler<//username>
<Time>1518881897868< /Time><Rating>5< /Rating>< Text>
An absolute must place to go in Palm Springs. It is right off the main drag but its secluded setting transports you out of the city and into a lovely farmhouse setting. Breakfast here is a must and reservations are encouraged. You can always put your name on the list and they will text you when your table is ready so you can wonder around town.

If you are there on select days don't miss the dinner. It's a fixed menu with a wonderful presentation. Sit back and enjoy a lovely meal just don't forget to make a reservation in advance.</Text>

< Text>
Worst dining experience in Palm Springs.  Went there for breakfast.  They seated us outside in the sun with flies buzzing around.  We asked for another table inside and were placed at a worn out metal cafe table.  The service was spotty.  We had to ask for water twice and we wound up "borrowing" silverware and napkins from an adjacent table.  The food was awful.  Waffles were cold, tasteless, and we had to ask for butter and syrup.  The toasted breakfast sandwich was served on a plate that appeared to just exit the dishwasher.  It was full of water and saturated the toast.  So much so that the sandwich fell apart when I picked it up.  The bloody mary was so laced with tobasco it was undrinkable.  Why people rate this place highly is beyond me.  We won't ever go back.  So many less expensive places with much better food and service.<//Text>

< user_name>
Deanna & Ricardo Sanabria<//user_name>
< Time>
1544860917341< /Time>
<rate>5<//rate>< Review>
This restaurant which was recommended by our sommelier at Le Vallauris was just a gem.  They have a beautiful courtyard and charming decor.  The service was attentive without being intrusive despite how busy they were.

The omelettes were outstanding and likely one could serve two as the portions were generous in fact I had my other half for dinner.  They do not scrimp in the ingredients and the omelettes were soft set and perfectly cooked.  I'm a big fan of French omelettes so this omelette was silky and creamy, not rubbery and browned as you so often find in other places.

I ordered a croissant and they served it charred and wow - what great flavor it imparted and the texture was still flakey, buttery and still lusciously soft!

We ordered a French press while waiting for breakfast and it was a great start to our meal.

If you want a great breakfast or brunch while in the area, you won't go wrong here!</Review>

<Text>Had dinner here last night and had a really nice time.  The $54 per head prix fixe presumably reflects the owners‚Äô target demographic and it was populated accordingly - with an older and more sophisticated crowd than many PS venues.   We had the oysters and grilled octopus appetizers and the vegetable curry and Coq Au Vin Entrees, followed by crepes and sorbet deserts.  Although the octopus lacked flavor, both the curry and the chicken were excellent, as were the crepes.   We added a delicious and reasonably priced ($40) bottle of Rose.
The venue (we sat outside even though it was 40 deg) is really pretty and reflects the South of France vibe they are going for.   Our server (Leah) was great and the discreet live music (Amber) was an added treat - beautiful voice with unusually confident restraint.
Definitely worth a visit.< /Text><resp>None</resp><userid>104084239258047112455</userid>< Pics>

</dataset><record>
<name>Shannon Murphy</name><GmapID>0x80db1ba5b4c5ed93:0x45a109b1119683e2</GmapID>< review>
I got the a la banane, which is French toast with sauteed bananas and mascarpone. The flavor was okay but it was lacking in the sweetness you'd typically find in French toast. Disappointing.
My brother got the chicken and mushroom crepe, and he and I were most disappointed by the fish, as it lacked flavor. The most flavorful part of this dish was the mushrooms, and even those were the least flavorful mushrooms I've ever tasted.
Some redeeming qualities of this establishment was it's unique ambience, and the kind and interesting staff. We felt like we really were at a farm in Paris. We were impressed by the silverware, which was actually from France--the knives had Little metal bees on them. Cute.</review>

The food was incredible, the surroundings charming in the extreme, and the service impeccable and impatient. We were taken care of and accommodated at every turn by Sarah and the fabulous kitchen staff during our late lunch.

Visit Farm at your earliest convenience.<//Review>
